4. Write a program that determines the distance to a lightning strike based on the time elapsed
between the flash and the sound of thunder. The speed of sound is approximately 1100 ft/sec
and 1 mile is 5280 ft.
--------
# File: 1.3-hands-on-practice-4
# Made 12.26.18 by Ksenia Z
# This program evaluates the distance of a lightning strike.

def main():
    print("This program calculates the distance of a lightning strike.")
    time = eval(input("How many seconds passed between the time of the thunder and lightning? "))
    distance = time * (1100 / 5200)
    print("The lightning strike is",round(distance, 2),"miles away")
main()
